4.12	Giovanni_Battista_Bugatti	Giovanni Battista Bugatti	Giovanni Battista Bugatti (1779â€“1869) was the official executioner for the Papal States from 1796 to 1865. He was the longest-serving executioner in the States and was nicknamed Mastro Titta, a Roman corruption of maestro di giustizia, or master of justice. At the age of 85, he was retired by Pope Pius IX with a monthly pension of 30 scudi.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/f/f7/Mastro_Titta.jpg
